<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="763" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[2004,2601,1030,1458]" pageId="5" pageNumber="763">
This speciesis sister to 
<taxonomicName box="[2326,2457,1117,1142]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Glischropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="763" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aquilus">G. aquilus</taxonomicName>
, although it is morphologically most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chasen" authorityYear="1939" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Glischropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="763" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="javanus">G. javanus</taxonomicName>
. The name batjanus from Bacan Island in the 
<collectingCountry box="[2182,2312,1228,1261]" name="Indonesia" pageId="5" pageNumber="763">Moluccas</collectingCountry>
has been regarded as a distinct species or a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1875" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Glischropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="763" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tylopus">G. tylopus</taxonomicName>
, but is here regarded as synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1875" box="[2008,2134,1345,1378]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Glischropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="763" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tylopus">G. tylopus</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="763" type="distribution">
